</taxonomicName>
[sic]: Poole, 1989: 674, misspelling.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="964A0933C100FFE926F6F16F7AE5F88B" blockId="0.[151,1436,1701,2030]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C100FFE926F6F16F7B54F8AA" authority=": Wang, 2001: 56" authorityName=": Wang" authorityPageNumber="56" authorityYear="2001" box="[151,517,1795,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharota">
<emphasis id="A481D521C100FFE926F6F16F7806F8AA" box="[151,343,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Naarda blepharota</emphasis>
: Wang, 2001: 56
</taxonomicName>
, figs (male 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C100FFE92419F16F7B82F8AA" box="[632,723,1795,1819]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">holotype</typeStatus>
, upper and under sides); 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C100FFE925ADF16F7DAAF8AA" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[972,1275,1795,1819]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref3670" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2014 a) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 1. Taxonomic notes and description of 28 new species from Asia. Oriental Insects, 48 (1 - 2), 1 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2014.959790" type="journal article" year="2014">Tóth &amp; Ronkay, 2014a: 33-34</bibRefCitation>
, figs 36 (female genitalia), 80 (female); 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C100FFE927D7F14E7B97F88B" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[438,710,1826,1850]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" pagination="3 - 23" refId="ref3813" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2015 a) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 2. Description of ten new species from Asia. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 61 (1), 3 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.17109 / AZH. 61.1.3.2015" type="journal article" year="2015">Tóth &amp; Ronkay, 2015a: 19</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 7 (male genitalia).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DEEF5AB8C100FFE826F6F12A7CDDFE36" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="592" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="964A0933C100FFE926F6F12A7B0DF8EF" blockId="0.[151,1436,1701,2030]" box="[151,604,1862,1886]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">
Distribution: 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C100FFE92747F12A7825F8EF" box="[294,372,1862,1886]" name="Taiwan" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="5431C7D1C100FFE927E3F12A789CF8EF" box="[386,461,1862,1886]" country="Taiwan" name="Chiayi" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Chiayi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="5431C7D1C100FFE927B9F12A7B00F8EF" box="[472,593,1862,1886]" country="Taiwan" name="Kaohsiung" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Kaohsiung</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="964A0933C100FFE826A6F1067CDDFE36" blockId="0.[151,1436,1701,2030]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1437,151,392]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="592" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">
Notes. This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C100FFE9243EF1067BA5F833" author="Strand E." box="[607,756,1898,1922]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" pagination="102 - 197" refId="ref3554" refString="Strand E. (1920) H. Sauter's Formosa-ausbeute: Noctuidae II Nebst nachtragen zu den familien Arctiidae, Lymantriidae, Not- odontidae, Geometridae, Thyrididae, Pyralidae, Tortricidae, Gelechiidae und Oecophoridae. Archiv Naturgeschichte, 84 A (12), 102 - 197." type="journal article" year="1920">Strand (1920)</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of a single male specimen from Suisharyo [
<materialsCitation id="269D036EC100FFE926F6F1E27CCDF87B" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3778508303" collectionCode="DEIM" country="Taiwan" location="Wang" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Chiayi" typeStatus="holotype">
Shuisheliao, 
<collectingRegion id="5431C7D1C100FFE92687F1E27861F817" box="[230,304,1934,1958]" country="Taiwan" name="Chiayi" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Chiayi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C100FFE9275BF1E278DFF817" box="[314,398,1934,1958]" name="Taiwan" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
]. 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C100FFE927FCF1E27B78F817" author="Wang, H. Y." box="[413,553,1934,1958]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" refId="ref4025" refString="Wang, H. Y. (1994) Noctuidae. Guide book to Insects in Taiwan 8. Shu Shin Books, Taipei, 477 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1994">Wang (1994)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated a female under the name of “ 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C100FFE925B7F1E27DF0F817" authorityName=": Wang" authorityYear="2001" box="[982,1185,1934,1958]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharota">
<emphasis id="A481D521C100FFE925B7F1E27DF0F817" box="[982,1185,1934,1958]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Naarda blepharota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, but doubtlessly it is a different species. 
<location id="932A5FE8C100FFE92733F1DE78C1F87B" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:1E5CB825C100FFE826F6F0C97CDDFE36:932A5FE8C100FFE92733F1DE78C1F87B" box="[338,400,1970,1994]" country="Taiwan" name="Wang" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" stateProvince="Chiayi">Wang</location>
(2001) illustrated the 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C100FFE9241BF1DE7B86F87B" box="[634,727,1970,1994]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species preserved in 
<collectionCode id="F0E491F6C100FFE92260F1DE7D18F878" box="[1025,1097,1970,1993]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">DEIM</collectionCode>
. In the revision of 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C100FFE9236CF1DE7CCDF87B" authority=", Toth &amp; Ronkay (2014 a)" authorityName=", Toth &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="2014" box="[1293,1436,1970,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A481D521C100FFE9236CF1DE7C0FF87B" box="[1293,1374,1970,1994]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Naarda</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C100FFE9230BF1DE7CCDF87B" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[1386,1436,1970,1994]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref3670" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2014 a) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 1. Taxonomic notes and description of 28 new species from Asia. Oriental Insects, 48 (1 - 2), 1 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2014.959790" type="journal article" year="2014">Tóth</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</materialsCitation>
&amp; Ronkay (2014a) described the female of 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C100FFE9240BF1BA7BACF85F" authorityName=": Wang" authorityYear="2001" box="[618,765,2006,2030]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharota">
<emphasis id="A481D521C100FFE9240BF1BA7BACF85F" box="[618,765,2006,2030]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">N. blepharota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without giving details about how to determine the conspecific status but they did not show any evidence of the identification of this species, they also examined one HNHM female “with data same as 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C101FFE82709F6D77899FF62" box="[360,456,187,211]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">holotype</typeStatus>
, not dissected”, this case is peculiar since to our best knowledge there is no other specimen of Strand’s Taiwanese species deposited outside DEIM and as the mention above Strand described this species through a single male specimen. In addition, 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE82443F76F7A74FEAA" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[546,805,259,284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="3 - 23" refId="ref3813" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2015 a) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 2. Description of ten new species from Asia. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 61 (1), 3 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.17109 / AZH. 61.1.3.2015" type="journal article" year="2015">Tóth &amp; Ronkay (2015a)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE822E3F7687C47FEAA" authorityName=": Wang" authorityYear="2001" box="[1154,1302,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharota">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE822E3F7687C47FEAA" box="[1154,1302,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">N. blepharota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without any specimen data except for the genitalia slide number (RL 
<quantity id="510DA4D6C101FFE82488F74B7A12FE8E" box="[745,835,295,319]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0745" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" unit="m" value="10745.0">10745m</quantity>
). Further, one of the reviewers, Dr. László Ronkay, kindly re-confirmed that the genitalia with slide number (RL 
<quantity id="510DA4D6C101FFE8248EF7277A19FED2" box="[751,840,331,355]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0745" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" unit="m" value="10745.0">10745m</quantity>
) illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE82583F7277D8CFED2" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[994,1245,331,356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="3 - 23" refId="ref3813" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2015 a) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 2. Description of ten new species from Asia. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 61 (1), 3 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.17109 / AZH. 61.1.3.2015" type="journal article" year="2015">Tóth &amp; Ronkay (2015a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7) is actually that of the 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C101FFE8276BF703783BFE36" box="[266,362,367,391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">holotype</typeStatus>
, “ 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE827E1F7037B3CFE36" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1920" box="[384,621,367,391]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Rhynchina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blepharota">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE827E1F7037B3CFE36" box="[384,621,367,391]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Rhynchina blepharota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m., Strand det, 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C101FFE82576F71C7A26FE36" box="[791,887,368,391]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Formosa</collectingCountry>
, Suisharyo, X.11, H. Sauter”, deposited in DEIM.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
